comments: Haliburton (IND) initiates body contact with VanVleet (HOU) that affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Nesmith (IND) establishes himself in VanVleet's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the pick is set.
Turner (IND) is extending slightly as he firms up over his left foot in Smith Jr.'s (HOU) path and he does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Eason (HOU) initiates contact with Turner's (IND) left arm and affects his dunk attempt.
Turner (IND) and Sengun (HOU) engage and disengage with one another off-ball in the post.

Holiday (HOU) raises his right arm up as he pursues the rebound and marginal contact occurs with the side of Haliburton's (IND) head prior to Haliburton deflecting the ball away. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Nesmith (IND) establishes himself in VanVleet's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the pick is set.
Turner (IND) establishes himself in Smith Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the pick is set.
Turner (IND) brings his hands toward Sengun's (HOU) side and marginal contact occurs as Sengun moves to set the pick.
Turner (IND) briefly places a hand on Sengun's (HOU) left shoulder before cleanly blocking the dunk attempt.  The contact before the blocked shot is marginal.
Turner (IND) cleanly blocks the dunk attempt when Sengun (HOU) still possesses the ball, and therefore is allowed to make contact with the ball while it is in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Hield (IND) and VanVleet (HOU) mutually engage and disengage with one another as they each pursue the rebound.
Hield's (IND) right foot avoids stepping out of bounds after he secures the rebound along the baseline.
Nembhard (IND) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Eason (HOU) jumps forward and is turning slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Nembhard (IND) as they come together after the release of the floater attempt.
Turner (IND) moves forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Eason (HOU) during Eason's upward shooting motion.

Tate (HOU) initiates contact across Turner's (IND) right arm after Turner secures the rebound. The crew communicated with the Replay Center to determine the correct free throw shooter and after review, Turner would shoot the free throws.
Hield (IND) legally contests Smith Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot attempt.
